But I think there’s an even deeper shift.

Mathematics is not the equations.

It’s the space of constraints.

A theorem isn’t merely true because someone proved it.

It’s true because there is no remaining freedom.

The proof removes every possible escape route until only one structure survives.

Meaning emerges from eliminated possibility.

